In 11 days, it will be 7 years since I lost Shalynne. I am not the first and will not be the last to suffer from our corporate-funded political system. I will not forget my promise - I will not tire out - I will continue to fight for us - we are all in this together!

Our campaign was able to connect with so many people from different communities and open minds to the possibility of demanding transformational change.  As with any fight for justice, it will be a long road.

Although we lost a battle on June 14th, the fight continues for Medicare for All, Economic Justice, Immigration Justice, GND, and fighting back against all forms of oppression. 

Thank you to all of those that supported my campaign, it was instrumental in reaching hearts & minds.
